{"id":38,"parent_id":31,"book_id":2,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":38,"title":"Mark 7","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mark","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 7"],[".studySummary",["i","Jesus reproves the Pharisees for their false traditions and ceremonies—He casts a devil out of the daughter of a Greek woman—He opens the ears and loosens the tongue of a person with an impediment."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.1","order":"03.04.007.4634"},["b","1"],"Then came together unto him the Pharisees, and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.2","order":"03.04.007.4635"},["b","2"],"And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread with defiled, that is to say, with unwashen, hands, they found fault."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.3","order":"03.04.007.4636"},["b","3"],"For the Pharisees, and all the Jews, except they",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"wash"],["i","their"],"hands oft, eat not, holding the tradition of the elders."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.4","order":"03.04.007.4637"},["b","4"],"And",["i","when they come"],"from the market, except they wash, they eat not. And many other things there be, which they have received to hold,",["i","as"],"the washing of cups, and pots, brasen vessels, and of tables."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.5","order":"03.04.007.4638"},["b","5"],"Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him, Why walk not thy disciples according to the tradition of the elders, but eat bread with",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"unwashen"],"hands?"],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.6","order":"03.04.007.4639"},["b","6"],"He answered and said unto them, Well hath Esaias prophesied of you hypocrites, as it is written, This people",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"honoureth"],"me with",["i","their"],"lips, but their heart is far from me."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.7","order":"03.04.007.4640"},["b","7"],"Howbeit in vain do they worship me, teaching",["i","for"],"doctrines the commandments of men."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.8","order":"03.04.007.4641"},["b","8"],"For laying aside the commandment of God, ye hold the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_8a"},"tradition"],"of men,",["i","as"],"the washing of pots and cups: and many other such like things ye do."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.9","order":"03.04.007.4642"},["b","9"],"And he said unto them, Full well ye reject the commandment of God, that ye may keep your own tradition."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.10","order":"03.04.007.4643"},["b","10"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_10a"},"For"],"Moses said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and, Whoso",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_10b"},"curseth"],"father or mother, let him die the death:"],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.11","order":"03.04.007.4644"},["b","11"],"But ye say, If a man shall say to his father or mother,",["i","It is"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"Corban"],", that is to say, a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me;",["i","he shall be free."]],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.12","order":"03.04.007.4645"},["b","12"],"And ye suffer him no more to do ought for his father or his mother;"],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.13","order":"03.04.007.4646"},["b","13"],"Making the word of God of none effect through your tradition, which ye have delivered: and many such like things do ye."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.14","order":"03.04.007.4647"},["b","14"],"¶And when he had called all the people",["i","unto him,"],"he said unto them, Hearken unto me every one",["i","of you,"],"and understand:"],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.15","order":"03.04.007.4648"},["b","15"],"There is nothing from without a man, that entering into him can",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"defile"],"him: but the things which come out of him, those are they that",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_15b"},"defile"],"the man."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.16","order":"03.04.007.4649"},["b","16"],"If any man have ears to hear, let him hear."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.17","order":"03.04.007.4650"},["b","17"],"And when he was entered into the house from the people, his disciples asked him concerning the parable."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.18","order":"03.04.007.4651"},["b","18"],"And he saith unto them, Are ye so without understanding also? Do ye not perceive, that whatsoever thing from without entereth into the man,",["i","it"],"cannot defile him;"],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.19","order":"03.04.007.4652"},["b","19"],"Because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly, and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats?"],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.20","order":"03.04.007.4653"},["b","20"],"And he said, That which cometh out of the man, that",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_20a"},"defileth"],"the man."],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.21","order":"03.04.007.4654"},["b","21"],"For from within, out of the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_21a"},"heart"],"of men, proceed evil thoughts,",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_21b"},"adulteries"],", fornications, murders,"],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.22","order":"03.04.007.4655"},["b","22"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_22a"},"Thefts"],",",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_22b"},"covetousness"],",",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_22c"},"wickedness"],",",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_22d"},"deceit"],", lasciviousness, an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness:"],["div",{"id":"23","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.23","order":"03.04.007.4656"},["b","23"],"All these",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_23a"},"evil"],"things come from within, and",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_23b"},"defile"],"the man."],["div",{"id":"24","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.24","order":"03.04.007.4657"},["b","24"],"¶And from thence he arose, and went into the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and entered into an house,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_24a"},"and"],"would have no man know",["i","it:"],"but he could not be hid."],["div",{"id":"25","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.25","order":"03.04.007.4658"},["b","25"],"For a",["i","certain"],"woman, whose young daughter had an unclean spirit, heard of him, and came and fell at his feet:"],["div",{"id":"26","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.26","order":"03.04.007.4659"},["b","26"],"The woman was a Greek, a Syrophenician by nation; and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil out of her daughter."],["div",{"id":"27","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.27","order":"03.04.007.4660"},["b","27"],"But Jesus said unto her, Let the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_27a"},"children first"],"be filled: for it is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast",["i","it"],"unto the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_27b"},"dogs"],"."],["div",{"id":"28","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.28","order":"03.04.007.4661"},["b","28"],"And she answered and said unto him, Yes, Lord: yet the dogs under the table eat of the children’s crumbs."],["div",{"id":"29","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.29","order":"03.04.007.4662"},["b","29"],"And he said unto her, For this saying go thy way; the devil is gone out of thy daughter."],["div",{"id":"30","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.30","order":"03.04.007.4663"},["b","30"],"And when she was come to her house, she found the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_30a"},"devil"],"gone out, and her daughter laid upon the bed."],["div",{"id":"31","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.31","order":"03.04.007.4664"},["b","31"],"¶And again, departing from the coasts of Tyre and Sidon, he came unto the sea of Galilee, through the midst of the coasts of Decapolis."],["div",{"id":"32","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.32","order":"03.04.007.4665"},["b","32"],"And they bring unto him one that was deaf, and had an impediment in his speech; and they beseech him to put his",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_32a"},"hand"],"upon him."],["div",{"id":"33","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.33","order":"03.04.007.4666"},["b","33"],"And he took him aside from the multitude, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spit, and touched his tongue;"],["div",{"id":"34","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.34","order":"03.04.007.4667"},["b","34"],"And looking up to heaven, he sighed, and saith unto him, Ephphatha, that is, Be opened."],["div",{"id":"35","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.35","order":"03.04.007.4668"},["b","35"],"And straightway his ears were",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_35a"},"opened"],", and the string of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plain."],["div",{"id":"36","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.36","order":"03.04.007.4669"},["b","36"],"And he charged them that they should tell no man: but the more he charged them, so much the more a great deal they",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_36a"},"published"],["i","it;"]],["div",{"id":"37","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.37","order":"03.04.007.4670"},["b","37"],"And were beyond measure astonished, saying, He hath done all things well: he maketh both the deaf to hear, and the dumb to speak."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.3a","order":"03.04.007.4671"},["b","3a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/purification"},"TG Purification"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.5a","order":"03.04.007.4673"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/wash"},"TG Wash"],"."],["div",{"id":"6a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.6a","order":"03.04.007.4675"},["b","6a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/apostasy-of-israel"},"TG Apostasy of Israel"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/hypocrisy"},"Hypocrisy"],"."],["div",{"id":"8a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.8a","order":"03.04.007.4677"},["b","8a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/traditions-of-men"},"TG Traditions of Men"],"."],["div",{"id":"10a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.10a","order":"03.04.007.4679"},["b","10a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst-mark/7.10-12"},["span.small","JST"],"Mark 7:10–12 (Appendix)"],"."],["div",{"id":"10b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.10b","order":"03.04.007.4681"},["b","10b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/curse"},"TG Curse"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/honoring-father-and-mother"},"Honoring Father and Mother"],"."],["div",{"id":"11a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.11a","order":"03.04.007.4683"},["b","11a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/15.5"},"Matt. 15:5"],"."],["div",{"id":"15a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.15a","order":"03.04.007.4685"},["b","15a"],["span.small","JST"],"Mark 7:15 … defile him,",["i","which is food;"],"but the things which come out of him; those are they that defile the man,",["i","that proceedeth forth out of the heart."]],["div",{"id":"15b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.15b","order":"03.04.007.4687"},["b","15b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/1.15"},"Titus 1:15"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/19.17"},"2 Ne. 19:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.35"},"D&C 93:35"],"."],["div",{"id":"20a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.20a","order":"03.04.007.4689"},["b","20a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/3.6"},"James 3:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.121"},"D&C 88:121"],"."],["div",{"id":"21a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.21a","order":"03.04.007.4691"},["b","21a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-jn/2.16"},"1 Jn. 2:16"],"."],["div",{"id":"21b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.21b","order":"03.04.007.4693"},["b","21b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/adulterer"},"TG Adulterer"],"."],["div",{"id":"22a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.22a","order":"03.04.007.4695"},["b","22a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/stealing"},"TG Stealing"],"."],["div",{"id":"22b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.22b","order":"03.04.007.4697"},["b","22b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/covet"},"TG Covet"],"."],["div",{"id":"22c","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.22c","order":"03.04.007.4699"},["b","22c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/wickedness"},"TG Wickedness"],"."],["div",{"id":"22d","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.22d","order":"03.04.007.4701"},["b","22d"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/deceit"},"TG Deceit"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/fraud"},"Fraud"],"."],["div",{"id":"23a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.23a","order":"03.04.007.4703"},["b","23a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/motivations"},"TG Motivations"],"."],["div",{"id":"23b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.23b","order":"03.04.007.4705"},["b","23b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.30"},"Mosiah 4:30"],"."],["div",{"id":"24a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.24a","order":"03.04.007.4707"},["b","24a"],["span.small","JST"],"Mark 7:22–23 … and would",["i","that"],"no man",["i","should come unto him."],"But he could not",["i","deny them; for he had compassion upon all men."]],["div",{"id":"27a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.27a","order":"03.04.007.4709"},["b","27a"],["span.small","JST"],"Mark 7:26 … children",["i","of the kingdom"],"first …"],["div",{"id":"27b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.27b","order":"03.04.007.4711"},["b","27b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/41.6"},"D&C 41:6"],"."],["div",{"id":"30a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.30a","order":"03.04.007.4713"},["b","30a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/11.31"},"1 Ne. 11:31"],"."],["div",{"id":"32a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.32a","order":"03.04.007.4715"},["b","32a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/administrations-to-the-sick"},"TG Administrations to the Sick"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/hands-laying-on-of"},"Hands, Laying on of"],"."],["div",{"id":"35a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.35a","order":"03.04.007.4717"},["b","35a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/miracle"},"TG Miracle"],"."],["div",{"id":"36a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/mark/7.36a","order":"03.04.007.4719"},["b","36a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.31"},"Matt. 9:31"],"."]]}
